<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id62c8436d-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s3907"><num value="3907">§ 3907.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id62c8436e-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s3907/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> General authorization</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated such sums as may be necessary to carry out this chapter.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id62c8436f-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s3907/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Coordination</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The activities required to be performed by the Director under this chapter shall be coordinated with activities related to solid waste and sanitation facilities funded pursuant to other authorizations.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id62c84370-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/103/399/s8">Pub. L. 103–399, § 8</ref>, <date date="1994-10-22">Oct. 22, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/4168">108 Stat. 4168</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
